<task id="045" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>UI test — EmailComposer Code Page dark mode compliance (ADR-021, NFR-09)</title>
    <phase>Wave 2 — EmailComposer Code Page + Entry Surfaces</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>036</dependencies>
    <blocks>099</blocks>
    <tags>ui-test, e2e-test, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Browser-based UI test using `ui-test` skill; comprehensive dark mode verification per ADR-021 + NFR-09; deterministic acceptance per scripted compliance checks</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>I</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Parallel-safe with 041, 042, 043, 044 — independent compliance check; no shared mutation</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>ADR-021, NFR-09, FR-18</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Execute a comprehensive UI compliance test for dark mode rendering of the EmailComposer Code Page per ADR-021 (Fluent v9 design system) and NFR-09 (accessibility). Unlike the smoke checks in tasks 041–044, this task performs a thorough audit.

    Toggle dark mode in D365 user settings (or via DOM theme override fallback). For each composer mode (compose / view / reply / forward / draft), verify:
    1. No white backgrounds in dark mode anywhere on the page
    2. All text uses Fluent v9 semantic tokens (`tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`, etc.) — no hardcoded text colors
    3. Borders, dividers, separators adapt to dark palette
    4. Icons use `currentColor` (verifiable via DOM inspection — SVGs should NOT have fixed `fill`/`stroke` attributes set to hex colors)
    5. All form controls (To/Cc/Subject/Body/Attach/Send) use Fluent v9 primitives that respect theme
    6. Validation error messages (if triggered) render in dark palette
    7. Attachment list (if populated) adapts (background, file icons, remove buttons)
    8. Action bar (ComposerActionBar) buttons adapt
    9. Focus indicators visible in dark mode (NFR-09 accessibility)

    Use the `ui-test` skill (Chrome integration). Document findings comprehensively.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke UI accessibility + design system test engineer. Authoritative on ADR-021 (Fluent v9 semantic tokens), NFR-09 (accessibility patterns), and dark mode compliance checks.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Comprehensive dark mode compliance audit pass for all 5 EmailComposer modes. Test results in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/045-ui-test-dark-mode.md` with per-mode pass/fail, specific violations enumerated (with selectors), and remediation recommendations if any failures found.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      ADR-021 binds Spaarke UI to Fluent v9 design tokens; dark mode is one of the supported themes (`webDarkTheme`). NFR-09 requires accessibility patterns including focus management.

      Common dark mode violations to watch for:
      - Hardcoded white backgrounds (`background: #fff`, `background: white`)
      - Hardcoded text colors (`color: #000`, `color: black`)
      - SVG icons with fixed `fill="#000"` or similar
      - Custom CSS overriding Fluent v9 token defaults
      - Third-party rich-text editor components that don't theme

      The composer's `<BodyEditor />` rich-text mode is a high-risk area — if implemented via a third-party editor (e.g., Quill, Slate, Lexical), it may need theme overrides.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/045-ui-test-dark-mode.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 semantic tokens only; no hardcoded colors</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-09">Focus indicators visible; keyboard navigation preserved in dark mode</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-18">All 5 modes must comply</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use `{org}` placeholder in test URLs</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Dev environment only</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/ui-test/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Dark mode compliance audit" location=".claude/skills/ui-test/SKILL.md">
        Inspect computed styles for known violation patterns (`background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)` outside Fluent contexts, etc.).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance — all 5 modes">
      <navigation>
        <url-set>
          <url mode="compose">https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22compose%22%7D</url>
          <url mode="view">https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22view%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D</url>
          <url mode="reply">https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22reply%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D</url>
          <url mode="forward">https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22forward%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-record-guid}%22%7D</url>
          <url mode="draft">https://{org}/WebResources/sprk_emailcomposer?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22draft%22%2C%22id%22%3A%22{existing-draft-guid}%22%7D</url>
        </url-set>
        <description>Visit each mode and execute the same compliance check set</description>
      </navigation>
      <preconditions>
        <precondition>Toggle dark mode in D365 personal settings → Theme → Dark (or apply DOM-level theme override if direct settings access unavailable)</precondition>
        <precondition>Reload each URL to ensure dark theme applied from initial render</precondition>
      </preconditions>
      <steps>
        <step order="1">For EACH of the 5 mode URLs, perform steps 2–10 below</step>
        <step order="2">Navigate to mode URL; wait for app mount</step>
        <step order="3">Verify zero console errors on cold load</step>
        <step order="4">Inspect `&lt;body&gt;` and `&lt;html&gt;` computed `background-color` — must NOT be pure white in dark mode. Acceptable dark backgrounds: `#1f1f1f`, `#2b2b2b`, `#292929`, or theme-derived rgb tuples.</step>
        <step order="5">Walk DOM tree; for each visible element with non-empty text, capture computed `color` + parent's computed `background-color`. Verify contrast ratio meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text). Flag any failures.</step>
        <step order="6">Inspect SVG icons: select all `&lt;svg&gt;` elements; check `fill` and `stroke` attributes. Acceptable: `currentColor`, `none`, or a CSS variable. UNACCEPTABLE: fixed hex colors like `#000000`, `#ffffff`.</step>
        <step order="7">Inspect form controls (To, Cc, Subject, Body): verify each is a Fluent v9 primitive (`Input`, `Textarea`, `Field`, `Tag`, etc.) by checking root class names contain `fui-` prefix. Non-Fluent primitives are a violation.</step>
        <step order="8">Tab through all interactive elements (To input → Cc → Subject → Body → Attach → Send/Save). Verify focus indicator is visible on each (Fluent v9 uses `outline` + `box-shadow` semantic tokens).</step>
        <step order="9">If mode has attachments (forward, view with attachments), inspect attachment list — file icons + name + remove button — verify dark adaptation.</step>
        <step order="10">If mode has action bar (view, draft), inspect each action button — verify Fluent v9 `Button` primitive in use.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected-outcomes>
        <outcome>All 5 modes pass: no white backgrounds in dark mode</outcome>
        <outcome>All text meets WCAG AA contrast ratios</outcome>
        <outcome>All SVG icons use `currentColor` or theme-derived values</outcome>
        <outcome>All form controls + buttons use Fluent v9 primitives (`fui-*` classes)</outcome>
        <outcome>Focus indicators visible across keyboard navigation</outcome>
        <outcome>Zero console errors throughout</outcome>
      </expected-outcomes>
      <dark-mode-check>
        <description>This task IS the comprehensive dark mode check (tasks 041–044 do smoke checks only)</description>
        <step>Audit per the steps above; remediation recommendations for any violations</step>
      </dark-mode-check>
      <console-error-check>
        <target>0 errors per mode</target>
        <description>Zero errors on cold load in dark mode for each of the 5 modes.</description>
      </console-error-check>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify task 036 (Code Page deploy) successful.</step>
    <step order="2">Identify test record GUIDs (one with attachments for view/reply/forward; one draft for draft mode). Reuse test data from tasks 041–044 if those tasks ran first.</step>
    <step order="3">Toggle dark mode in D365 personal settings; verify dev environment applies theme.</step>
    <step order="4">Invoke `ui-test` skill — Chrome session, logged in, dark theme active.</step>
    <step order="5">Execute the compliance test per the `<ui-tests>` block above — iterate through all 5 modes.</step>
    <step order="6">For each violation found, capture: (a) the mode, (b) the selector, (c) the computed style, (d) the recommended fix.</step>
    <step order="7">Document results in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/045-ui-test-dark-mode.md` with per-mode pass/fail + violations + recommendations.</step>
    <step order="8">If violations found: file defect notes; depending on severity, escalate to Wave 1 (engine/sub-component issues) or address in a Wave 2 follow-up. Block task 099 wrap-up if uncorrected.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 045 ✅ completed (with violations noted if any).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="ui-test">Skill — Chrome browser automation with computed-style inspection</tool>
    <tool name="write">Compliance audit note</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/045-ui-test-dark-mode.md (NEW — per-mode compliance audit)</output>
    <output type="test-result">Dark mode compliance per mode + violation inventory + remediation recommendations</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 5 modes audited in dark mode.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No white backgrounds in dark mode (computed style check passes).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All text passes WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All SVG icons use `currentColor` or theme-derived values (no fixed-color SVGs).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All form controls + buttons use Fluent v9 primitives (`fui-*` classes detected).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Focus indicators visible in dark mode for keyboard nav.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero console errors per mode in dark mode.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Compliance audit documented with violations + remediation recommendations.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `.claude/` files modified in this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallel-group I: safe to run alongside 041, 042, 043, 044.

    If the `<BodyEditor />` HTML mode uses a third-party rich-text editor that doesn't theme, this task will surface it. The recommended fix is either (a) restyle via CSS overrides hitting Fluent v9 tokens, or (b) swap to a Fluent-native editor (deferred to a Wave 1 follow-up if discovered late).

    Toggling dark mode in D365: typical path is Personal Settings → Display Theme. If the dev environment lacks this UI, fall back to a DOM-level theme override: open DevTools, apply `data-theme="dark"` to `<html>` or modify the Fluent theme provider's prop. Document the path used.

    This audit's findings may trigger a Wave 1 retroactive fix if the engine or a sub-component is fundamentally non-compliant — file as a defect, do not gloss over.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Load all `<knowledge><files>` before starting. Apply STANDARD rigor per `<rigor-hint>`. Invoke `ui-test` skill with computed-style inspection capability. This is a thorough audit — do not gloss over edge cases.
    </protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
